    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the \"live in the moment\" thing but it feels like just a way to distract yourself from the math. if you know for a fact that any progress or joy we experience is just 0 eventually, then why bother with the struggle? the struggle is the only thing that actually hurts. if the end result is always going to be nothing, then why is it better to suffer through the middle part instead of just skipping to the end? it feels like we're just prolonging the inevitable for no reason.",
